CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "Club Officers - New officers of the Young Women's Civic Club were installed by The Courier's women's editor, Toki Schalk Johnson at a swank luncheon at the New Arena Club last Friday afternoon. Seated, left to right: Mrs. Jeremiah Ingram, vie president; Mrs. Matthew H. Dempsey, president; Mrs. Eugene Cobb, financial secretary.  Standing: Mrs. George Henderson, chaplain; Mrs. John Birt, assistant secretary and reporter; Mrs. Max Johnson, treasurer, and Mrs. Nathaniel Woods, secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: New officers of the Young Women's Civic Club, seated, left to right: Mrs. Jeremiah Ingram, Mrs. Matthew H. Dempsey, and Mrs. Eugene Cobb;  standing: Mrs. George Henderson, Mrs. John Birt, Mrs. Max Johnson, and Mrs. Nathaniel Woods, gathered at table in New Arena Club
